Lenza midway through the third peri-
od broke the Panthers’ backs. V

The Dukes went on an offensive,

tear, as Browne scored three goals in
four minutes to send Ciarletta to the

bench.‘ Patrick Kenny, who was sup-'

posed to have the nightvoff, came in
after the fifth goal and surrendered

- three more late in the final period.

“The third period, it was just a
letdown,” Ciarletta said. “We let by
shorthanded breakaways a couple
times and you can’t do that. I think
overall I played a strong game, but
the game might have been a lot dif-
ferent if we had come out strong.”

Pitt’s seasonal record drops to 2-
13, and Chouinard has just one goal
in mind for the rest of the year.

“I know I’d like to walk out of
the season with three wins, and I
hope we can pull it together, step up
and start winning,” he said, “because
it’s a really good feeling.”

Pitt travels to Washington, D.C.
Friday to take on the George
Washington University Colonials,
and is scheduled to return home

Valentine’s Day weekend to take on

West Virginia.

